text: The South-Eastern Metropolitan Region is an electoral region of the Victorian Legislative Council, the upper house of the Victorian Parliament. It is located in the southeastern part of Melbourne. The region includes the Legislative Assembly (lower house) electoral districts of Berwick, Carrum, Clarinda, Cranbourne, Dandenong, Frankston, Mordialloc, Mulgrave, Narre Warren North, Narre Warren South and Rowville. ==Election results== 9,334 1.99 -1.11 ==References== Category:Electoral regions of Victoria Category:2006 establishments in Australia
